  "text": "We only review the idea here. For more details the reader is referred to Glynn and L'Ecuyer (1993). We rst assume that m = 1, but will consider the case m > 1 shortly. Let us write P(x; ) = (x)'( ) + (1 ? (x))Q(x; ); [CITATION_1] where Q(x; ) is given by",
